You are a senior full-stack engineer.  Generate a complete Next.js (v14+) + Tailwind CSS starter codebase with Supabase (Postgres) for auth and data, implementing:

---

### 1. Supabase Schema & Auth

1. **Tables:**
   - **users**  
     • id (uuid, PK)  
     • email (text, unique)  
     • role (enum: 'admin','paid_user','free_user')  
     • created_at (timestamp)  
   - **domains**  
     • id (serial, PK)  
     • name (text, unique)  
   - **questions**  
     • id (serial, PK)  
     • domain_id (FK → domains.id)  
     • text (text)  
     • options (jsonb) — array of exactly four strings or objects `{ text, imageUrl? }`  
     • correctAnswer (char) — one of 'A','B','C','D'  
     • explanation (text, nullable)  
   - **tests**  
     • id (uuid, PK)  
     • user_id (FK → users.id)  
     • domain_filter (int[] nullable) — list of domain IDs, or null for “all”  
     • started_at, completed_at (timestamps)  
     • score_total (int), score_by_domain (jsonb { domainId:score })  
   - **attempts**  
     • id (uuid, PK)  
     • test_id (FK → tests.id)  
     • question_id (FK → questions.id)  
     • selectedAnswer (char)  
     • time_spent (int seconds)  

2. **Auth & RLS:**  
   - Use Supabase Auth for email/password + social.  
   - Row-Level Security policies:  
     • users see only their tests/attempts.  
     • admins can CRUD everything.  

---

### 2. Student-Facing App

- **App Router** structure (`/app`):  
  - `/login`, `/signup`, `/dashboard`, `/tests/new`, `/tests/[id]`, `/questions/page/[page]`, `/admin/*`  
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS with mobile-responsive layout.  
- **State:** use React redux to hold current test timer + answers.  
- **Data Fetching:** Supabase JS SDK + SWR for client-cached queries.

#### Quiz UI

- **Pagination:** 20 questions/page; URL `?page=1`, `?page=2`, etc.  
- **Question Card:**  
